text: This happend to me as a child, physical abusive from my father. Its hard to watch this trailer, but God is restoring the long lost love he has for me. Unfortunately the physical abusive effected the relationship i had with God for years. Until CR, 12 steps. Almost 30 years it took before I could start to enjoying God's love with no strings attached to it. This movie trailer reminds me of not giving up on life which i tried many times as a child. God never left my side and pursued me my whole life, nothing i did ever pushed him away. God's pursuit for love in my life between him and I is why i am here writing this. He never gave up on me, and I hope and encourage others to ponder on that. My tears were his tears, my pain was his pain, my anger was his anger, my laughter was his laughter. Never imagined God would be so close to me through all of this.

text: Alright, this may sound odd but I have a very personal connection to this song and this movie surprises and amazes me to be coming out now. Years ago my grandfather (who basically raised me because my parents were still in high school) passed away. For his funeral I played this song on guitar while singing in front of the church. I broke down once and had to start over but I'm glad i did it.  Fast forward to a few weeks ago. I've been basically living with my girlfriend and her parents for the past 4.5 years and got close to her family. Recently her mom passed away pretty suddenly. I decided I would play "I Can Only Imagine" for her funeral as well since she loved when when I played guitar or piano for her and because of how special the song is to me. That funeral was on Sunday, three days ago. I just learned today that a movie of the making of this song was coming out and in TWO DAYS.   I'm probably just being emotional but this seems very special to me. I'm not normally a very religious person but maybe this movie can be special to me just like the song is. Anyway, thank you anyone who took time to read my story. No real purpose to this, I just felt like writing and sharing. Looking forward to seeing this like most of you!
author: Christian Kurtz

text: this really isn‚Äôt a good movie. my 8th grade went to the movies today and it really just wasn‚Äôt good.  //// spoilers, if you don‚Äôt want to read, don‚Äôt    there was barely any build up. this movie could have been really good if it actually tried.  in the beginning, when the mom left, it gave no emotion. i sort of shrugged it off because we didn‚Äôt know the character too well. this scene could have been extremely powerful if it would have built up, if we learned she was barts only support system or if we saw them have more interaction and more interest in the relationship. but no, sadly there was absolutely no build up to that scene. things like this are sprinkled throughout the movie; how we aren‚Äôt shown that the father tried to mend the relationship until they mended their relationship. we didn‚Äôt even know the father sent letters. i feel as if it would have been more interesting to see Bart receive the letters, through them away, and be deeply affected by it, since it did mention he received them but threw them out. and, i don‚Äôt know if this is because i‚Äôm atheist, but how his transformation from abusive to loving was solely because he became religious/ god helped him, is extremely cheap. we didn‚Äôt see the father try to fix himself, or even assert that he had a problem. i can understand this IS a religious movie, but if we saw him assert he had an issue and decide to become religious because he needed something to motivate him, i would have been completely fine with that. instead, we are given barely any information of how he fixed himself other than he went to church.. i don‚Äôt know.. maybe i‚Äôm thinking way to far into this :/ oof

text: This song has so touched me for many years. We can only imagine. Heaven is something that even the best dreams have not dreamed. This song will always be special . I lost my mother almost 2 years ago. I miss her ,  she is in heaven with her father now. 7 years ago I had went to Tennessee for my 4th year anniversary. I phoned my mother and her and my father came to Tennessee to see the timeshare that I had purchased while I was there.  I took my mother to a movie and a show there and this was the song that it was all done around. I will never forget this memory. Now that she has went home, I can only image what she is doing up there with God. One day I will join her there and get to finally know what I could only imagine. When I purchased the time share , I assumed there would be plenty of family vacations to follow. Life is a funny thing, and it is given by God . The bible says we must call upon his name to be saved, repent of our sins and know that it is only by the shedding of the blood of Jesus that we are saved. He died on the cross for our sins and arose the 3 day. We could never imagine the pain and suffering he  went through , the bible says that There was hardly any flesh let on his bones. Now just imagine how much he loves us. Then goes to prepare a place for us to live with him for ever. Wow can you imagine?

text: God tells us to honor our mother and father. Part of honoring includes not calling them "monsters" in public. You can tell God they're monsters and he'll help you deal with that, but you don't say it publicly. This is a huge problem with people who call themselves Christians -- they engage in a lot of parent-bashing. The Commandments are non-negotiable. We're to honor our parents, not bash them, no matter what they've done to us or anyone else. In other words, if you can't say anything nice about them, don't say anything at all. No if's, and's or but's. The Commandments are non-negotiable. Honor your mother and father.

text: Following a dream is not what God wants for His believers.  The disciples left all to follow Jesus, immediately!  They left everything.  They suffered and were hungry, they were cold, they were persecuted.  Don't let hollywood sell you anything less than what God expects of you.   Don't let them sell you an emotional ride that inhibits the truth, dazzles the eyes, tickles the ears.  You are to follow Him and not your dreams.  Unless you leave everything you cannot be a follower of Christ.  As Jesus Himself said, you don't build a house unless you count the cost.  The same applies in following Jesus.  It's not about YOU, it's about Him.  Satan was cast out because he was full of himself.  If you are full of yourself and your selfish desires and dreams you will not see the kingdom, period!  Hollywood is selling you a lie!  Ask the Father in all things.  Trust Him in all things. text: Mind power to give you what you imagine is increased by waking up the brain. The fact that if I forget something, like a name, and later remember it again proves that we do only use a lesser percentage of our brains. By increasing the percentage of our brain use we increase our power to get what we want by imagining it. "Normal" brain use is only 10% brain use. From 30% to 40% brain use whatever we write will become our reality. From 40% to 50% brain use whatever we say will become our reality. But, from 50% to 100% brain use everything we think will become our reality, and, who can control every thought? Parasympathetic nervous system stimulation, e.g. vagal stimulation, increases your percentage of brain use, by over riding the brain's inhibitory neurons. This has been the most suppressed secret in history.

text: Ok I don't think the guy who wrote this song will ever see this comment but it's the way i found Jesus! Quite honestly i found salvation..... Life.... Because when i was 11 and in his same situation i was alone, i had been sexually abused, and completely broken. I'll never forget sitting on my bedroom floor crying wondering at 11 years old what the point of taking my next breath was when i turned on the radio, cause all i had at the time was music and poetry it was all i had to express what I'd been through was to write songs, i flipped through the stations and I heard the melody to that song play so i stopped and heard that song play and I knew Jesus Christ himself was speaking to me the words themselves had NOTHING to do with what i was going through but i broke down screaming cause it was the 1st time i knew that God loved me I had no idea of the background to the song but i knew God was holding me from the inside of my soul to the outside of my body. So hearing the story behind it is ministering to my situation now reminding me of that very first moment i had with my Abba Father and how he never lets go, he knew my pain then and he knows it now and will always carry us through if we just let him. He's the love of my life and i will not let him go!! Hallelujah Abba we adore you!
author: Daisy Harris

This film touched in to my spirit in so many ways that I can't even explain ..I watched it before my Father became ill. I praise God in Jesus Christ for my Father's life and the impact he has made it on me and my family, he was a strong man who loved Jesus and he was a warrior in every sense of the word.
